body:
For future reference:

This doesn't work because the tcp_posix poller that's scheduled to executor is long-lived, which can block other executor work items for executing indefinitely.

Possible solutions:
1. have a 'long running' tag for executor work items: such tags would block out any job queuing by other threads
2. isolate tcp polling work in the tcp code, and keep a special thread pool there
I suspect this is ready for review
